    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9800 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - DOOR VENT WINDOW
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>DOOR VENT WINDOW</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>The door vent window is held in the door frame by three pan head screws and hex head bolt.</para>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1601861">Figure 61</hotlnk>
                for Items in parentheses.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1601861" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1601861" filename="../figg16/G1601861.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 61. Door Vent Window</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. DOOR WINDOW FRAME</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. BUTTON PLUG/MOUNTING SCREW</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. BUTTON PLUG/CHANNEL BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. DOOR VENT WINDOW</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove door glass and door window seals from door. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16018_20.xml" xrefid="hl1601805">CAB DOOR GLASS, Remove
                        <xref refid="hl1601805"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    , and
                    <hotlnk document="s16018_22.xml" xrefid="hl1601807">CHANNELS AND SEALS, Remove
                        <xref refid="hl1601807"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">At outside edge of door window frame (Item 1), remove 3 button plugs (Item 2), 2 in
                    front edge and 1 on top, for access to vent window mounting screws. Remove 3 screws.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove button plug (Item 3) from inner door frame and remove upper channel bolt (Item
                    3), now exposed.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift door vent window (Item 4) out of door window frame (Item 1).</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install door vent window (Item 4) into door window frame (Item 1).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install upper channel bolt (Item 3) in inner door frame. Do not tighten at this time.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install 3 mounting screws (Item 2) at outside edge of door window frame (Item 1), 2 in
                    front edge and 1 on top, securing door vent window (Item 4). Do not tighten.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With door vent window (Item 4) in proper position, tighten 3 mounting screws (Item 2)
                    and upper channel bolt (Item 3) and insert button plugs (Items 2 and 3).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install door window seals and door glass. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16018_22.xml" xrefid="hl1601808">CHANNELS AND SEALS, Install
                        <xref refid="hl1601808"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    , and
                    <hotlnk document="s16018_20.xml" xrefid="hl1601806">CAB DOOR GLASS, Install
                        <xref refid="hl1601806"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
